Package org.opennars.storage

Class Memory

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.opennars.storage.Memory
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Iterable<Concept>, Resettable
    public class Memory
extends Object
implements Serializable, Iterable<Concept>, Resettable
    Memory consists of the run-time state of a Nar, including: * term and concept memory * reasoner state * etc.
    Excluding input/output channels which are managed by a Nar.
    A memory is controlled by zero or one Nar's at a given time.
    Memory is serializable so it can be persisted and transported.
    See Also:
    Serialized Form

      • conceptualize

        public Concept conceptualize​(BudgetValue budget,
                             Term term)
        Get the Concept associated to a Term, or create it. Existing concept: apply tasklink activation (remove from bag, adjust budget, reinsert) New concept: set initial activation, insert Subconcept: extract from cache, apply activation, insert If failed to insert as a result of null bag, returns null A displaced Concept resulting from insert is forgotten (but may be stored in optional subconcept memory
        Parameters:
        term - indicating the concept
        Returns:
        an existing Concept, or a new one, or null
